The paper deals with metric embeddings of graphs, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and discrete mathematics. The use of shortest path decompositions and treewidth suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The mention of probabilistic embeddings suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT), while the use of $\ell_p$ spaces suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the mention of embeddings on graphs excluding a minor suggests a connection to structural graph theory (cs.SI).
